text: von Düben [fɔn dy:ʹbən] is a Swedish noble family that comes from Germany. The family is famous for its musical contributions. Most of the members of the von Düben family lives in Mexico as of today. == Notable people == * Gustaf Düben (1628–1690), composer and organist * Emerentia von Düben (1669–1743), lady-in- waiting, the favourite of Ulrika Eleonora, Queen of Sweden == References == Category:Swedish noble families
title: Von Düben
